        Official Singles Chart on 3/9/2021

        3 September 2021 - 9 September 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        The thing I have observed with streaming affecting the charts, is a song can linger in the top 100 for months, in some rare cases years, Blinding lights for example 92 weeks inside the top 100, but the reality and disadvantage of this is it doesn't allow new music or artists to keep the charts fresh.
        If we rewind back to the 80's for example to have a single linger in the charts for more than 20 weeks max was unheard of as most people would have either heard it on the radio and already bought it by then, so something else would have taken its place.
        Streaming has definetly slowed down progression of new music because so many songs are stagnant inside the top 100.
        Fleetwood Mac has been in the charts with Dreams for months on and off but God knows why, the song is over 40 years old.
        The industry needs a serious shake up, before the charts become a waste of time.
